<section xml:id="SIMILAR-TRIANGLES" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>SIMILAR TRIANGLES</title>

  <p> You can use  <em>“similar triangles”</em> to compute angles, lengths, or forces of two triangles that are considered similar. </p>
  <p> For example, to solve for X in the diagram, we can use similar triangles (if the angles in the triangle are the same). </p>
  <example xml:id="similar_triangles_example_1">
    <p>
      <m>\frac{5}{12} = \frac{10}{x}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
      So <m>x =</m> 24'
    </p>
</example>
